flowRoot.flowPara: A TL494 PWM generator IC is connected to external components (in blue) as shown. Use the datasheet for this chip (available on Moodle) to answer the following questions:
1. What is the frequency, shape and amplitude of the waveform at pin 5 (CT pin)? (Hint: See section 9.3.2)
2. What is the average voltage across the two 10k resistors?
The circuit is modified and now pin 13 is pulled high (5V) by connecting it to pin 14.
1. What is the average voltage across the two 10k resistors now?
2. What is the time between a falling edge on pin 9 and rising edge on pin 10?

A buck converter is shown above. It is desired that the duty cycle of the MOSFET be proportional to the modulating voltage vm(t), which can range from 0V (d=0%) to 12V (d=100%). Further, it is desired that turn-off transition be modulated, i.e. the the MOSFET must turn ON at the same time in each switching cycle, but turn off must be based on the modulating voltage.

Sketch vc(t) and the contents of the "?" block to make this happen. You may use only ideal op-amps / comparators. You may assume for this problem, that a "high" output of a comparator is sufficient to drive the gate of MOSFET and thereby turn it on.
